result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel J. Helgeson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Resisting an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

(Cases called at 11:30 AM - 21CF1331, 21CT276, 21CT292, 21CT337, 22CF490)
Defendant Daniel Helgeson appears in custody with Attorney Robert Thorson.  Attorney Tiffany Winter appears for the State of Wisconsin.
State in compliance with victim notification requirements.  Agreement reached and recited by the State.  Plea Questionnaire acknowledged.  Defendant advised of elements and maximum possible penalties of the offenses to which he will plead.  Basis for Repeater enhancer acknowledged.  Defendant pleads No Contest to: 21CF1331 Count 1: Identity Theft - Avoidance; 21CT276 Count 1: Operating While Revoked; 22CF490 Count 2: Possession of Methamphetamine (Repeater) and Count 4: Resisting an Officer (Repeater).  Defendant advised of his Constitutional rights.  Court accepts pleas and finds Defendant guilty of the offenses to which he has pled.  Everything else is dismissed and read-in, to include any ride-along traffic citations and the entirety of 21CT292 and 21CT337).  Defendant makes a statement.  As to 21CF1331 and Count 2 in 22CF490, Court withholds sentence and orders 5 years probation with the following conditions: 180 days in jail (on both cases concurrent, with Huber) stayed pending further order of the Court.  Undergo AODA assessment and follow-through with recommendations (assessment to be completed within first 6 months of probation).  No contact with anyone involved in illegal drug activities except in a therapeutic setting.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  No entry into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, or any place that primarily serves alcohol.  Not to possess any illegal drugs, drug paraphernalia, or prescription medications not prescribed to him.  Comply with any conditions/programming per agent.  34 days sentence credit if revoked from probation.
As to 21CT276 and Count 4 in 22CF490, Court orders court costs only.  Contraband is ordered destroyed.
Plea hearing on May 31, 2022 at 11:30 am.
